From 499c45a2de723bc16b7f403a1e86c950012f8c8e Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Amith A <amitajit@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Mon, 11 Aug 2025 10:15:36 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM:PROTOCOL: wifi: ath12k: Set 6 GHz band_mask flag for
 regd updates due to AFC

When a 6 GHz interface is initially brought up in LPI power mode and
transitions to SP mode upon receiving an AFC response, the AP behaves
as expected. However, if the 6 GHz interface is subsequently brought
down and a 5 GHz interface is brought up on a DFS channel, a later AFC
response causes the 5 GHz interface to go down after one minute. This
unexpected behavior stems from how the AFC response handling updates
the regulatory domain (regd). Specifically, the regdomain is
intersected with the AFC power values, triggering regd_update_work,
which calls handle_band_custom() for all bands. This leads to\
handle_channel_custom() clearing channel flags for every channel,
including the radar flag on DFS channels. Later, reg_check_channels()
schedules delayed work to validate active channels. Since the radar flag
was cleared, the DFS channel is deemed invalid, resulting in stop_ap
being triggered and the 5 GHz interface being shut down.

To fix this issue, set the band_mask in regd with the 6 GHz flag when
regd update is triggered due to AFC. This ensures that only 6 GHz channels
are updated when regd update is triggered from AFC.

Fixes: None
Patch-work: None
Tag: 6G_REGULATORY
Feature: AFC
Path-dependency:
0376-UPSTREAM-PROTOCOL-wifi-ath12k-Handle-switch-to-LPI-a.patch
0380-d-UPSTREAM-PROTOCOL-wifi-ath12k-Build-new-regd-after-A.patch
subsys/0346-UPSTREAM-PROTOCOL-wifi-cfg80211-add-band_mask-to-reg.patch

Signed-off-by: Amith A <amitajit@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/reg.c | 3 ++-
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/reg.c b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/reg.c
index 78d9e13..33dbdca 100644
--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/reg.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/reg.c
@@ -1489,6 +1489,7 @@ static int ath12k_handle_invalid_afc_payload(struct ath12k *ar)
 	ath12k_dbg(ab, ATH12K_DBG_AFC, "Queuing NO-IR regd update work for pdev %u\n",
 		   ar->pdev_idx);
 	ah->regd_updated = false;
+	regd->band_mask = BIT(NL80211_BAND_6GHZ);
 	queue_work(ab->workqueue, &ar->regd_update_work);
 	return ret;
 }
@@ -2397,7 +2398,7 @@ ath12k_reg_build_new_regd_for_afc(struct ath12k *ar,
 						       num_afc_ranges,
 						       no_ir_ranges,
 						       num_no_ir_ranges);
-
+	new_regd->band_mask = BIT(NL80211_BAND_6GHZ);
 	*regd_afc = new_regd;
 
 	return 0;
